description:
&lt;p&gt;Whittington Health Trust are looking for enthusiastic full time bank radiographers to join our professional and friendly team. This is a great opportunity to ‘try before you buy’ with a strong likelihood of permanent employment for exceptional candidates in 2020. Our patient experience feedback is overwhelmingly positive and this is because of the cohesion and team spirit of the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Hospital site has 2 back to back MRI scanners, 2 CT scanners, 7 digital x-ray rooms, 3 new DR mobiles, a brand new SPECT CT scanner, DEXA scanner, fluoroscopy and interventional fluoroscopy suite sited in theatre as well as several US rooms. Over 200,000 exams will be performed this year and a large scale equipment replacement programme due to finish this this year has seen installation of all new Samsung DR x-ray rooms, a new CT scanner, mammography unit and fluoroscopy machine as well as replacement of our US units.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospital site is well served by transport links being next to Archway tube station and a 10 min walk from Upper Holloway Overground dtation as well as being served by multiple bus routes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recent changes mean that Advanced Practice is now supported within Imaging as part of the 5 Year forward view and working pattern changes are now embedded in order to further promote Advanced Practice and enhance the quality aspect of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Any appointee will be expected to contribute to idea generation and the promotion of collaborative working across professional groups and inter-departmentally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participation in an AfC compliant rota will be expected with extended days forming part of the working pattern.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential requirements are:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;HCPC Registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 months NHS experience in a similar role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
